            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Job 36</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="1" xml:id="Job-036-001"><seg type="commented" corresp="#Job--seg001"
                                 /><supplied reason="lost">Da qaruv berdi Elihu da
                                ajtty.</supplied><anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg001"
                                 /><ref n="1" target="#Job-036-fn1" type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <l n="2" xml:id="Job-036-002">Syj qojġun <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Job--seg002" /><foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            tözgün<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg002" /><ref n="2"
                                target="#Job-036-fn2" type="noteAnchor" /> mana azɣynaq da anlatajym
                            sana ki hanuz bardy Tenri<addSpan spanTo="#Job-036-add001" /><addSpan
                                spanTo="#Job-036-add001" />ge<anchor xml:id="Job-036-add001"
                                type="addSpan" /><anchor xml:id="Job-036-add002" type="addSpan"
                                 /><ref n="3" target="#Job-036-fn3" type="noteAnchor" /> üčün
                            sözler.</l>
                        <l n="3" xml:id="Job-036-003">Kötürejim aqylymny
                            <milestone unit="page" n="102v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" />
                            jyraqqa da jaratuvčumnun qotarajym rastlyɣyn.</l>
                        <l n="4" xml:id="Job-036-004">Ki kertiden jalɣan tüvüldü sözlerim tügel
                            aqylly qatynda.</l>
                        <l n="5" xml:id="Job-036-005">Muna Tenri küčlüdü da ḥor etmejdi küčlü da kip
                            jüreklü.</l>
                        <l n="6" xml:id="Job-036-006">Tiri tutmajdy rašaʿany vale töresin
                            miskinlernin beredir.</l>
                        <l n="7" xml:id="Job-036-007">Ketermejdi cadiqten ʿenajatlaryn da ošol
                            bijlerni mindiredir taḥtqa da olturɣuzady alarny ömü<addSpan
                                spanTo="#Job-036-add003" />r<anchor xml:id="Job-036-add003"
                                type="addSpan" />gedejin da ullu
                            <milestone unit="page" n="103r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" />
                            boladylar.</l>
                        <l n="8" xml:id="Job-036-008">Da eger tutqun bolsalar buɣovlar byla
                            ilinseler qyjynly avlarɣa.</l>
                        <l n="9" xml:id="Job-036-009">Da anlatady alarɣa išlerin da güneḥlerin ki
                            küčejseler.</l>
                        <l n="10" xml:id="Job-036-010">Da ačady qulaqlaryn tyjuvɣa da ajtady ki
                            qajtqajlar avanlyqtan.</l>
                        <l n="11" xml:id="Job-036-011">Eger tynlasalar da qulluq etseler upratyrlar
                            künlerin jaḥšylyq byla da jyllaryn čeberlikler byla.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="103v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="12" xml:id="Job-036-012">Da eger tynlamaslar qylyč ašyra tüšerler da
                            tynarlar aqylsyz.</l>
                        <l n="13" xml:id="Job-036-013">Da azɣan jürekliler qojadylar ačuv firjat
                            etmejdiler ki tutqun etti alarny.</l>
                        <l n="14" xml:id="Job-036-014">Eler telilik byla ǯanlary da tirlikleri
                            taraturluqta.</l>
                        <l n="15" xml:id="Job-036-015">Qutqarady miskinni miskinligi üčün da
                            ašqartady qysyqlyqta qulaqlaryna.</l>
                        <l n="16" xml:id="Job-036-016">Da hem keteredi seni tar jerde
                            <milestone unit="page" n="104r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" />
                            toḥtatma seni ken jerde qysyq tüvül tübü any qojar ornun stolunnun tolu
                            nametten.</l>
                        <l n="17" xml:id="Job-036-017">Da jarɣusundan rašaʿnyn tolsan jarɣunu da
                            töreni ki tutadylar sende tutsan <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Job--seg003" /><foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר פשט ב׳ </foreign>
                            jarɣu da töre kipler<addSpan spanTo="#Job-036-add004" />ler<anchor
                                xml:id="Job-036-add004" type="addSpan" /> seni<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg003" /><ref n="4"
                                target="#Job-036-fn4" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="18" xml:id="Job-036-018">Ki eger ačuvlansa maɣat keterir seni
                            ḥyššymybyla da köp juluv almas senin üčün.</l>
                        <l n="19" xml:id="Job-036-019">Tüzülirmo malyn senin ki bolmaɣajsen tarlyqta
                            da bar küčlü mal.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="104v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="20" xml:id="Job-036-020">Küsenmegin ol kečeni kesme uluslarny
                            orunlarynda.</l>
                        <l n="21" xml:id="Job-036-021">Saqlanɣyn qajrylmaɣyn avanlyqqa ki bunu
                            sajlarsen telilikten.</l>
                        <l n="22" xml:id="Job-036-022">Muna Tenri kiplejdi küčü byla kim anyn kibik
                            jamɣur berivčü.</l>
                        <l n="23" xml:id="Job-036-023">Kim vakil eter anar jolun da kim ajtyr qyldyn
                            avanlyq.</l>
                        <l n="24" xml:id="Job-036-024">Saɣynɣyn ki ullu tutqun išin anyn neni ki
                            kerdiler erenler.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="105r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="25" xml:id="Job-036-025">Bar adam köredi any kiši baɣadyr
                            jyraqtyn.</l>
                        <l n="26" xml:id="Job-036-026">Muna Tenri ulludur da bilelmejbiz sanyna
                            jyllarynyn da joḥtur törgev<ref n="5" target="#Job-036-fn5"
                                type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="27" xml:id="Job-036-027">Ki eksilse tamčylary suvnun javadyr jamɣur
                            bulutundan.</l>
                        <l n="28" xml:id="Job-036-028">Ki tamyzdyradylar kökler javdyradylar adam
                            üstüne köp jamɣur.</l>
                        <l n="29" xml:id="Job-036-029">Ham ki anlajalyrmo jajylmaqlaryn bulutunun
                            čuvlamaqlaryn jabuvnun.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="105v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="30" xml:id="Job-036-030">Muna jajadyr bulutlar üstüne jamɣurun da
                            qorenlerin ol tengiznin qaplajdyr.</l>
                        <l n="31" xml:id="Job-036-031">Ki alar byla jarɣu jaradyr uluslarny beredir
                            jem köplerge <seg type="commented" corresp="#Job--seg004" /><foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר פ׳ ב׳ </foreign>
                            jetkiligiče<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg004" /><ref n="6"
                                target="#Job-036-fn6" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="32" xml:id="Job-036-032">Bulutlar üstüne qaplajdyr jamɣurnu da
                            saryjdyr anyn üčün joluɣuvču ašyra. <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Job--seg005" /><foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">ולפי דעת המתרגם </foreign>
                            Uvučlar qysqan üčün <supplied reason="lost">aja</supplied>dyr<ref n="7"
                                target="#Job-036-fn7" type="noteAnchor" /> jamɣurnu da bujuradyr
                            anar javma tefila etüvčü üčün.<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Job--seg005" /><ref n="8" target="#Job-036-fn8"
                                type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <l n="33" xml:id="Job-036-033">Anlatady jamɣurun da
                            <milestone unit="page" n="106r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" />
                            kök kökremegin tuvar ham balaly tuvar <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Job--seg006" /><foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר </foreign>
                            bulut kötürüledoɣan<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg006" /><ref
                                n="9" target="#Job-036-fn9" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-036-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 36:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 4:1, etc. for similar cases. We reconstruct
                            this verse on the basis of ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is not omitted,
                            see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וַיַּעַן
                                אֱלִיהוּ וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘And Job answered and said’ (Job 36:1). | C: <emph>Da arttyrdy Elihu da
                                ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da arttyrdy Elihu da ajtty</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>Da arttyrdy Elihu da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>Da arttyrdy Elihu da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-036-fn2" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>syj qojɣun</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">כַּתַּר </foreign>
                            ‘bear’, written after Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            ‘or’. | C: <emph>sabur etkin</emph>. | QB: <emph>sabur etkin</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>syj qojɣun </emph><foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או</foreign>
                            <emph> tezgin</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019): <emph>t́ozǵuń</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-036-fn3" type="footnote">Initially: <emph>Tenrige</emph>;
                            the word was corrected by not adding the vowel points to the
                            suffix.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-036-fn4" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>jarɣunu da töreni ki tutadylar sende tutsan</emph>, the
                            equivalent of BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >דִּין וּמִשְׁפָּט יִתְמֹכוּ </foreign>
                            ‘judgment and justice take hold on you’, added after Heb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר פשט ב׳ </foreign>
                            ‘or you will read a second interpretation’. | C: <emph>dinni da
                                šaraʿatny tutarlar</emph>. | QB: <emph>dinni da šaraʿatny
                                tutarlar</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>jarɣunu da töreni ki tutadylar
                                tutasen</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019): <emph>ki jarɣu da t́oŕa
                                bird́ań tutunadyrlar</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-036-fn5" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>tergev</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-036-fn6" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>köplerge</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">לְמַכְבִּיר </foreign>
                            ‘in abundance’, added after the Hebrew expression <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר פ׳ ב׳ </foreign>
                            ‘or you will say a second translation’. | C: <emph>köpkä</emph>. | QB:
                                <emph>köpkä</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>köplerge</emph>. |
                            Kobeckaitė (2019): <emph>baryna</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-036-fn7" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: <emph>jajadyr</emph>;
                            a scribal error, cf. the text in ADub.III.84 (see next footnote).</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-036-fn8" type="footnote">An explanation or alternative
                            translation of Job 36:31, added after Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">ולפי דעת המתרגם </foreign>
                            ‘and according to the translator’. Almost the same explatation is to be
                            found in ms. ADub.III.84. The additional text resembles the only
                            translation in C and QB: C: <emph>Bulutlar üstünä japty jamɣurny da
                                symarlady anyŋ učun tefila etivčigä</emph>; QB: <emph>Bulutlar
                                üstünä japty jaɣmurny da symarlady anyŋ učun tefila etivčigä.</emph>
                            | C: no alternative translation is offered. | QB: no alternative
                            translation is offered. | ADub.III.84: <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או ולפי דעת המתרגם </foreign>
                            <emph>Uvuclar qysqan üčün ajajdyr jamɣurnu da bujurady anar javma tefile
                                etivčü üčün</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019): no alternative translation
                            is offered.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-036-fn9" type="footnote">Most likely an alternative
                            translation to <emph>ham balaly tuvar</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb.
                                <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">עַל־עֹולֶה </foreign>
                            ‘concerning the rising (storm)’, added after Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר </foreign>
                            ‘or say’. | C: <emph>daɣyn čyɣaj turɣan ot üstünä</emph>. | QB:
                                <emph>daɣyn čyɣaj turɣan ot üstünä</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>hem
                                balalary tuvarnyn </emph><foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או</foreign>
                            <emph> bulut kötirinedoġan</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019): <emph>da
                                anlejdyr kelḿagiń anyn</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
